That is definitely not true, I-ra.
I've never once given up on you.

148
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:44,284
My heart has always been yours.

149
00:20:44,368 --> 00:20:45,661
Fuck. What are you on about?

150
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,121
I've finally realized

151
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,832
that you're the only woman in my life.

152
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:51,750
God.

153
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:55,128
Have you run out of money?

154
00:20:56,463 --> 00:20:59,466
I'm into someone else now,
you crazy bastard!

155
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,593
Hey, baby.

156
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:28,036
Can you take a look at this for me?
Is this how it's supposed to be?

157
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:31,957
-Right.
-I-ra.

158
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:38,088
Don't do this, I-ra. Let's start over.

159
00:21:38,171 --> 00:21:40,382
What are you doing? You're hurting me!

160
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:41,550
Please.

161
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,223
Just pay my wife back, asshole.

162
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,684
And hands off
if you know what's good for you.

163
00:21:54,646 --> 00:21:56,898
The sweet smell of money!

164
00:21:59,026 --> 00:21:59,901
Smell it.

165
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:05,741
Hey! Here!

166
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:09,494
You've got to do this.
One more time. Oh yeah.

167
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:12,956
One more time. Oh yeah!

168
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:53,705
Hi.

169
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:02,506
Are you back from visiting home?

170
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:05,258
Yes.

171
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:06,510
That's good.

172
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:11,348
When does break start?
You can take about a week off, right?

173
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:13,600
Shall we go abroad nearby?

174
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:17,312
Japan? Or Guam?

175
00:23:22,609 --> 00:23:23,735
When did you get back?

176
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:24,861
This morning.

177
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:28,657
-And how's your cold?
-I'm okay.

178
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:32,536
That's good.

179
00:23:34,162 --> 00:23:35,914
I'm going up. I'm tired.

180
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:38,834
Look, say what you want to say…

181
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:43,422
and stop being so frustrating.

182
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:49,386
If I say what I want to right now,
I'll regret it.

183
00:23:49,469 --> 00:23:50,720
So say it.

184
00:23:50,804 --> 00:23:53,014
I can take whatever you say.

185
00:23:56,643 --> 00:24:00,397
Ask me what I did with him.
That's what you want to know, isn't it?

186
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:01,898
-What?
-Why? Isn't it?

187
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:04,359
In your head,
you're imagining all sorts of things,

188
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:07,320
but you don't have the guts
to get mad at me.

189
00:24:08,655 --> 00:24:10,699
Is this your way of saying sorry?

190
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:13,994
Or are you not even sorry?

191
00:24:15,078 --> 00:24:17,539
What right do I have to get mad at you?

192
00:24:17,622 --> 00:24:20,417
I don't want to know
what you did with that guy.

193
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:23,128
What I want to know is
what you are doing with me.

194
00:24:23,712 --> 00:24:25,630
I thought it didn't matter to me

195
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:28,091
whether you're leaning on me
because you're lonely

196
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:29,342
or just playing around.

197
00:24:29,843 --> 00:24:33,597
Since I liked you and I was okay with it,
I thought it didn't matter.

198
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:40,020
But I guess I'm not that tolerant.

199
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:43,607
You don't have to have feelings for me.

200
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:45,525
Why would someone like you want to have…

201
00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:53,700
But this is going too far.

202
00:24:54,784 --> 00:24:55,785
Even for you.

203
00:25:18,225 --> 00:25:19,059
Hey, Won-jun,

204
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:22,854
you're staying here over winter break,
right? The landlady was asking.

205
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:26,191
I'll be moving out. I'll let her know.

206
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,027
What?

207
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:31,530
Really? Why?

208
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:26,960
Yes, I'm doing my best to sort things out.

209
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:30,380
I'll update you as soon as I have news.
I'm sorry.

210
00:26:45,061 --> 00:26:46,146
Why did you do it?

211
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:49,608
Lee Doona.

212
00:26:58,366 --> 00:26:59,743
I already told you.

213
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:04,497
I just can't sing.

214
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:09,628
Fine.

215
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:12,088
Then take a break.

216
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,075
Yes, Ms. Ma.

217
00:27:41,701 --> 00:27:42,827
It's not going to work.

218
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:45,664
We'll have to take Doona out
and continue with four.

219
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:47,040
I'm sorry.

220
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:21,366
Welcome.

221
00:28:55,692 --> 00:28:56,526
A milkshake?

222
