264
00:32:59,602 --> 00:33:03,064
Do you want to go there?
Everyone will want to see you.

265
00:33:06,776 --> 00:33:07,610
No.

266
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:12,115
You told me

267
00:33:12,615 --> 00:33:15,034
not to let anyone treat me badly.

268
00:33:15,618 --> 00:33:17,370
But when I thought about it,

269
00:33:17,453 --> 00:33:20,873
I realized I was the one
who mistreated myself most.

270
00:33:23,501 --> 00:33:26,629
I'm treating myself better
by not being friends with you.

271
00:33:28,339 --> 00:33:30,174
It still hurts, you see.

272
00:33:34,095 --> 00:33:35,221
Who knows?

273
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:39,559
With time, when there comes a point
when all I feel is joy when I see you,

274
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:42,603
maybe we can be friends then.

275
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:46,357
Please understand that,
even if you feel disappointed.

276
00:34:02,665 --> 00:34:05,334
In your head,
you're imagining all sorts of things,

277
00:34:05,418 --> 00:34:07,420
but you don't have the guts
to get mad at me.

278
00:34:09,338 --> 00:34:11,340
Is this your way of saying sorry?

279
00:34:13,176 --> 00:34:14,802
Or are you not even sorry?

280
00:34:15,595 --> 00:34:17,472
I thought it didn't matter to me

281
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:19,891
whether you're leaning on me
because you're lonely

282
00:34:19,974 --> 00:34:21,350
or just playing around.

283
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:25,521
Since I liked you and I was okay with it,
I thought it didn't matter.

284
00:34:28,274 --> 00:34:30,401
But I guess I'm not that tolerant.

285
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:50,630
Are you moving out?

286
00:34:51,214 --> 00:34:52,048
Yes.

287
00:34:52,548 --> 00:34:54,634
-Where to?
-I don't know.

288
00:34:55,885 --> 00:34:57,261
What if I told you not to?

289
00:35:00,973 --> 00:35:03,017
-Do I have to answer that?
-Yes, you do.

290
00:35:09,190 --> 00:35:10,525
Could you leave my room?

291
00:35:28,584 --> 00:35:30,962
Stop this. You smell of cigarette smoke.

292
00:35:31,045 --> 00:35:32,380
But I quit.

293
00:35:33,339 --> 00:35:35,091
Maybe it's his smell, then.

294
00:35:38,761 --> 00:35:40,096
You're a real jealous type.

295
00:35:41,222 --> 00:35:44,100
What? Does he not want you?

296
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:46,519
Is that why you need me again?

297
00:35:46,602 --> 00:35:48,813
I'd stop there,
while I still find it cute.

298
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:55,194
I'm staying here.

299
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:58,030
Drag me out if you can.

300
00:35:58,114 --> 00:36:00,491
I'm telling you
I want you out of my sight!

301
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:02,326
Why are you insisting on being here?

302
00:36:02,827 --> 00:36:03,995
Because I want company.

303
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:05,788
Which doesn't have to be me!

304
00:36:05,872 --> 00:36:06,706
It does.

305
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:09,458
It does have to be you.

306
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:17,758
Then why did you do that to me?

307
00:36:19,385 --> 00:36:20,636
Because I didn't know

308
00:36:22,263 --> 00:36:24,015
that the person I didn't want to lose…

309
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:27,226
was you.

310
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:31,647
I don't know a lot,

311
00:36:32,273 --> 00:36:35,276
and I'm always slow
at realizing my own feelings.

312
00:36:36,903 --> 00:36:39,071
I only find out
after I've lost everything.

313
00:36:39,655 --> 00:36:40,948
And then I regret it.

314
00:36:42,074 --> 00:36:43,826
It drives me crazy too.

315
00:36:45,745 --> 00:36:48,289
So, can't you go easy on me, please?

316
00:36:50,791 --> 00:36:53,252
You're a real mess. You know that?

317
00:36:54,128 --> 00:36:55,963
You're selfish and unstable,

318
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:58,299
and you hurt me without a second thought.

319
00:37:00,009 --> 00:37:01,636
That's why it feels so unfair.

320
00:37:02,136 --> 00:37:04,722
You're the one that came
and shook me up out of nowhere,

321
00:37:05,473 --> 00:37:06,849
but now, I'm the one

322
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:11,229
who wants you to be mine so much
it's driving me crazy.

323
00:37:16,859 --> 00:37:18,444
So tell me you're sorry.

324
00:37:23,282 --> 00:37:25,368
-I'm sorry.
-Tell me that you like me.

325
00:37:27,453 --> 00:37:29,872
Tell me that you like me and not him.

326
00:37:32,875 --> 00:37:33,751
Please.

327
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,547
I love you.

328
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:09,745
Won-jun.

329
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:11,831
Yeah?

330
00:38:13,082 --> 00:38:14,625
Don't hate me.

331
00:38:15,835 --> 00:38:16,961
I don't hate you.

332
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:21,966
I tried, but I couldn't.

333
00:38:23,884 --> 00:38:25,094
I don't mean now.

334
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:27,972
I mean going forward.

335
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:31,142
I promise I won't.

336
00:38:34,562 --> 00:38:36,397
Does this mean we've made up?

337
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:38,566
Yes.

338
00:38:40,026 --> 00:38:41,485
So easily?

339
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:46,532
I've always been easy.
I was just pretending to be difficult.

340
00:38:56,667 --> 00:38:59,170
It has to be you for me too.

341
00:39:17,271 --> 00:39:21,275
Do you remember the song
I gave up writing halfway through?

342
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,153
During our second album, I think.

343
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:28,491
I'd forgotten the melody,

344
00:39:29,909 --> 00:39:31,452
but it's come back to me.

345
00:39:34,914 --> 00:39:36,916
-That's good.
-It is.

346
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:42,213
To the point where I actually wonder
if it's okay to feel so good.

347
00:39:47,343 --> 00:39:49,095
You should drink that. You ordered it.

348
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:44,019
Subtitle translation by: Reuben Simpson

